$ git config

Get and set → development/version-control-systems/git/repository[repository] or global options.

code {
git config --global user.email "…"
git config --global user.name  "René Nyffenegger"

git config --global --get   user.email

git config --global --unset user.email
code }

{ --global, --user, --local

code {
git config --global …
git config --user   …
git config --local  …
code }

  `--user` for any «global» setting that is specific to a user.
  -
  `--local` for settings specific to a checked out → development/version-control-systems/git/repository[repository].

}


sa:
  → development/version-control-systems/git/commands
